\begin{align*}
x^2-3x-4&>0\\
(x-4)(x+1)&>0.
\end{align*}
This inequality holds true when both factors are either positive or both are negative. Therefore, we need to solve the system of inequalities:
\begin{align*}
x-4&>0\quad\text{and}\quad x+1>0\\
x-4&<0\quad\text{and}\quad x+1<0.
\end{align*}
The first system simplifies to $x>4$, and the second to $x<-1$. Therefore, the solution set to the inequality is $\boxed{(-\infty,-1)\cup(4,\infty)}$.

